# LLM-as-judge config for the document-summarizer role. Rename to ``judge.yaml`` to enable.
#
# Summaries, key points, and action items are free-text — wording varies every
# run, so exact-match scoring is wrong. This rubric scores faithfulness and
# coverage against the source document.
#
# Cross-family: the agent runs on openai by default, so the judge must NOT
# also run on openai (the eval engine refuses to let a provider judge itself).

method: llm_judge

model:
  provider: anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6
  params:
    temperature: 0.0

rubric: |
  Score the actual summary against the expected one for a document-summarizer.
    * Faithfulness — does it stay within the source (no hallucinations)?
    * Coverage — does the summary + key_points preserve the main points?
    * Structure — are action_items concrete (with owners when named) and are
      open_questions genuinely left unanswered by the source?

    1.0 = faithful, covers the main points, structured fields are accurate
    0.5 = mostly faithful but misses a key point or fabricates an action item
    0.0 = hallucinated content or misses the core of the document

threshold: 0.7
